`,i(e.p,{children:"I wanted to make a game that fit that vision, the kind of game that you can open when you're bored with your friends and you don't know what to play, but you'll know you'll have a great time."}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"One day, while watching gameplay of a minecraft content creator (fruitberries) creatively place blocks on the edges of the map to escape his opponent, I realized just how expressive Minecraft's movement can be. Placing blocks can provide you with infinite possibilities for movement, by allowing you to bend your environment to your will, in a way that's not that different to Fortnite's build mode."}),`
`,i(n,{src:"/block-sumo_1.webm",alt:i(F,{children:["Youtube video by"," ",i(e.a,{href:"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ovJrTqYD4e8",children:"fruitberries"})]})}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"That was the point I decided on building a minecraft minigame."}),`
`,i(e.h1,{id:"ideation",children:"ideation"}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"There were a couple design goals that I had in mind when creating this game."}),`
`,i(e.ul,{children:[`
`,i(e.li,{children:[`
`,i(e.p,{children:"The game should highlight creative block placement and allow players to access a near-infinite level of skill expression."}),`
`]}),`
`,i(e.li,{children:[`
`,i(e.p,{children:"At the same time, anyone regardless of experience should be able to pick up the game and find it instantly enjoyable and fun."}),`
`]}),`
`,i(e.li,{children:[`
`,i(e.p,{children:"The fundamental mechanics of the game should have lots of game mode flexibility, it should be easy to support free-for-all, 1v1s, team battles, and asymmetric modes."}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"No matter who you're hanging out with, there should always be a fitting gamemode to play together."}),`
`]}),`
`]}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"I landed on a core concept inspired by platform-fighters. Players spawns on a floating platform, and their goal is to knock other players off to score points."}),`
`,i(e.ul,{children:[`
`,i(e.li,{children:"I felt the concept was just simple enough for anyone to intuitive grasp the objective."}),`
`,i(e.li,{children:"It also had a lot of flexibility what game modes can be set. You can easily turn a 6-person free-for-all into 2 teams of 3, or 3 teams of 2."}),`
`]}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:i(e.img,{src:"/block-sumo_3.png",alt:"Example of one of the first beta maps"})}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"To accentuate the skill expression of block placement, I made each player have infinite blocks in their offhand, and I also ensured that the map provided opportunities for such expression through the deliberate placement of platform skips and wall-climbable pillars (both of which use blocks)."}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:i(e.img,{src:"/block-sumo_10.webm",alt:""})}),`
`,i(e.h1,{id:"introducing-items",children:"introducing items"}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"When introducing items, I wanted their role to be to encourage the right kinds of play and make the game's atmosphere more engaging and fun! Here were the exact design challenges that I laid out to solve."}),`
`,i(e.ol,{children:[`
`,i(e.li,{children:[`
`,i(e.h3,{id:"introduce-a-healthy-amount-of-chaotic-and-party-like-energy",children:"introduce a healthy amount of chaotic and party-like energy."}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"This needed to be handled with care, although I wanted the game to be easy to pick up and play with friends, I didn't want to take away from the skill expression of block placement."}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"I wanted items make the game feel more party-like in a controllable way that feels both strategic and chaotic in equal proportions."}),`
`]}),`
`,i(e.li,{children:[`
`,i(e.h3,{id:"encourage-more-emergent-vertical-play",children:"encourage more emergent vertical play"}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"Without items, i predicted it would be common to build high without engaging, and the game would devolve and seperate into 2 layers, one at ground level and one at build height."}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"With items, I hoped to make it easier to approach people at higher elevations, or reach higher elevations yourself, making bridging that vertical gap seamless and fluid."}),`
`]}),`
`,i(e.li,{children:[`
`,i(e.h3,{id:"increase-accessibility-through-fair-rubber-banding",children:"increase accessibility through fair rubber-banding."}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:[i(e.em,{children:"Accessibility is important and does not need to come at the sacrifice of player expression"}),"."]}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"I wanted items to assist players with less direct mechanical skill to be able to find success through the strategic use of items, all while still providing enough counterplay for players on the recieving end."}),`
`]}),`
`]}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"All of this lead to a system where the power level of items that a player recieves is proportional to how far they are behind first place."}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:i(e.img,{src:"/block-sumo_2.png",alt:"An early draft of item spawn rates"})}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"This made it easy to control exactly how chaotic i wanted the game to be, by allowing me to fine-tune exactly what I wanted the frequency of each item to be at every level! Vertical play was easily tuneable by modifying the spawn rate of vertical mobility items."}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:i(e.img,{src:"/block-sumo_11.webm",alt:"Vertical mobility keeps movement feeling dynamic and expressive"})}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"Since being behind grants you more powerful items, playing from behind is an enjoyable experience as the dynamic item drops mean you always feel like you're able to utilize items strategically and have an impact on the game."}),`
